The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 17th as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17th to September 23rd as Constitution Week. The proclamation highlights the significance of the United States Constitution as the foundation of the nation's government and protector of its liberties. It emphasizes the importance of civic engagement and encourages citizens to learn about and teach others about the Constitution. The proclamation also recognizes the diverse stories and heritages that contribute to the fabric of the nation and calls for ceremonies and programs to celebrate the Constitution and reaffirm citizens' rights and obligations.